<title>JAPAN: DKB president, chairman to resign--Kyodo.</title>
<headline>DKB president, chairman to resign--Kyodo.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank Ltd (DKB) president Katsuhiko Kondo and chairman Tadashi Okuda will step down to take responsibility for the bank's role in a scandal, Kyodo news agency reported on Friday.  </p>
<p>It said the bank has decided to appoint vice president Ichiro Fujita as president and another vice president, Yoshiharu Mani, as chairman, because of the bank's involvement in a racketeer payoff scandal at Nomura Securities Co Ltd .</p>
